1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:08,008
[clock ticking]

2
00:00:26,943 --> 00:00:32,073
A toast to my ascension
as new head of the Syndicate.

3
00:00:36,619 --> 00:00:37,746
You don't look happy, Julia.

4
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:40,415
This is what you wanted, isn't it?

5
00:00:42,042 --> 00:00:43,668
To be free of the Elders.

6
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:45,295
[sighs in exasperation]

7
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:46,818
- Vicious...
- [Vicious] Don't worry.

8
00:00:47,839 --> 00:00:49,215
Everything went to plan.

9
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:57,057
Just not the plan
you and Mao came up with.

10
00:00:57,140 --> 00:00:58,140
[inhales sharply]

11
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:00,894
I don't know what you're talking about.

12
00:01:00,977 --> 00:01:04,689
There is nothing
in this world to believe in.

13
00:01:06,357 --> 00:01:07,859
Least of all people.

14
00:01:10,028 --> 00:01:14,074
Even the people
who are supposed to love you.

15
00:01:14,783 --> 00:01:16,367
I do love you. [grunts]

16
00:01:17,243 --> 00:01:18,244
[sobbing]

17
00:01:19,954 --> 00:01:24,417
I always wondered,
how many times did you fuck Fearless?

18
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:27,170
[yells] How many?

19
00:01:28,630 --> 00:01:30,298
It was him, wasn't it?

20
00:01:30,381 --> 00:01:34,469
You found out Fearless is alive.
That's why you betrayed me. Isn't it?

21
00:01:38,556 --> 00:01:40,558
[laughing]

22
00:01:44,854 --> 00:01:46,397
It wasn't Fearless.

23
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:48,733
It was you!

24
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:52,821
[grunts]

25
00:01:53,613 --> 00:01:54,948
All of this time,

26
00:01:56,282 --> 00:01:58,535
I convinced myself
you couldn't have known.

27
00:01:59,244 --> 00:02:01,496
Because what kind of a man

28
00:02:02,330 --> 00:02:05,458
stays with a woman
who's slept with his best friend?

29
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:11,464
Oh, but of course you knew.
And you stayed.

30
00:02:13,508 --> 00:02:18,388
Because you are no man at all.

31
00:02:30,275 --> 00:02:32,735
I am gonna hurt you, Julia.

32
00:02:34,529 --> 00:02:37,073
In ways that haven't been invented yet.

33
00:02:37,699 --> 00:02:43,413
Until you beg me to kill you,
and then I'm gonna hurt you some more.

34
00:02:44,247 --> 00:02:45,248
Though...

35
00:02:47,417 --> 00:02:48,668
you won't be alone.

36
00:02:50,879 --> 00:02:54,841
You'll have Fearless' head
to keep you company.

37
00:03:02,182 --> 00:03:04,225
[theme music playing]

38
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:11,065
<i>I think it's time to blow this scene</i>

39
00:03:11,149 --> 00:03:13,193
<i>Get everybody and the stuff together</i>

40
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:15,778
<i>Okay, three, two, one, let's jam!</i>

41
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,291
[distorted laughter]

42
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:53,813
- [laughs maniacally]
- [Spike grunts]

43
00:05:00,341 --> 00:05:01,634
[screams]

44
00:05:02,593 --> 00:05:03,593
[panting]

45
00:05:10,018 --> 00:05:12,061
[Jet] Spike! Spike!

46
00:05:19,944 --> 00:05:20,945
Spike!

47
00:05:22,655 --> 00:05:23,656
Where the hell are you?

48
00:05:24,699 --> 00:05:27,910
<i>- Any sign of him on your end?</i>
- [Faye sighs] I've got jack.

49
00:05:28,536 --> 00:05:31,289
And for the record,
this place is creepy as shit.

50
00:05:31,956 --> 00:05:34,417
[Jet] <i>He's here somewhere, God damn it.
Keep looking for him.</i>

51
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:36,711
Spike!

52
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:00,109
Yeah!

53
00:06:03,196 --> 00:06:05,031
Oh, shit.

54
00:06:05,823 --> 00:06:07,784
[Jet] <i>Faye, I got something.</i>

55
00:06:08,368 --> 00:06:11,329
There was a ship here. Someone took Spike.

56
00:06:11,412 --> 00:06:13,998
Whoever it was,
we need to find the bastards.

57
00:06:14,957 --> 00:06:16,667
<i>Come on. Let's get outta here.</i>

58
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:47,656
[grunts]

59
00:06:48,366 --> 00:06:49,366
[groans]

60
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:52,202
[moans]

61
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:57,083
[breathing heavily]

62
00:06:58,626 --> 00:07:00,920
[jazz music playing]

63
00:07:10,138 --> 00:07:13,266
- Rough night?
- About the usual these days.

64
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,560
How did I get here?

65
00:07:17,937 --> 00:07:19,897
- Gren brought you in.
- With pleasure.

66
00:07:21,858 --> 00:07:22,978
[Spike] How did you find me?

67
00:07:23,568 --> 00:07:26,237
Lin and Shin still come in
from time to time.

68
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:29,073
I bugged Lin. A few weeks back.

69
00:07:29,157 --> 00:07:31,159
He always was the stupider of the two.

70
00:07:32,076 --> 00:07:33,916
I thought you had rules
about getting involved.

71
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:36,121
I do.

72
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:42,503
But you'd be dead otherwise.
And I couldn't let that happen.

73
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:44,839
Again.

74
00:07:49,552 --> 00:07:50,595
Again?

75
00:07:53,556 --> 00:07:57,393
Truth is, I've been involved
since the night they tried to kill you.

76
00:07:58,394 --> 00:07:59,394
And this...

77
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:03,649
This is not from getting old.

78
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:18,915
[young Faye] <i>You can do it, all right?</i>

79
00:08:18,998 --> 00:08:21,918
<i>Go me! Go me! Go me! Yay!</i>

80
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:24,212
[melancholic music playing]

81
00:08:58,329 --> 00:09:00,331
[beeping]

82
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:03,667
Yes!

83
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:09,233
- Jet. I think I found something.
- I found something.

84
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:10,466
Oh.

85
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:11,550
You first.

86
00:09:12,051 --> 00:09:15,221
The ship that took Spike.
A friend at Astral Gate Security,

87
00:09:15,304 --> 00:09:17,723
he matched the time stamp
and vessel registration.

88
00:09:17,807 --> 00:09:21,769
It just landed in Tharsis two hours ago,
next to a nightclub called "Ana's."

89
00:09:21,852 --> 00:09:22,979
What've you got?

90
00:09:23,896 --> 00:09:25,898
I think I might know where I grew up.

91
00:09:25,982 --> 00:09:26,983
Can it keep?

92
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:33,656
Because I need you on this.
Spike needs you on this.

93
00:09:34,574 --> 00:09:37,702
Once we get him back, we can help you
track your shit down. All of it.

94
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:40,955
We'll figure it out. Together.

95
00:09:45,710 --> 00:09:46,752
Let's go get Spike.

96
00:09:46,836 --> 00:09:48,838
- [woman on PA] <i>Bebop clearing hyperspace.</i>
- Deal.

97
00:09:48,921 --> 00:09:50,381
[woman on PA] <i>Arriving gateway...</i>

98
00:09:53,634 --> 00:09:54,927
<i>Bebop cleared.</i>

99
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:57,471
They were coming after me.
You can't blame yourself.

100
00:09:58,055 --> 00:10:01,475
I signed your death warrant that night.
Yours and Julia's.

101
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:03,394
You said Vicious put a sword
through your leg.

102
00:10:03,477 --> 00:10:05,521
The best of us would have broken.

103
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:10,568
Hey. I'm gonna find him.

104
00:10:11,986 --> 00:10:13,321
And I'm gonna kill him.

105
00:10:13,404 --> 00:10:16,574
You putting that miserable piece of shit
in the ground for good...

106
00:10:17,325 --> 00:10:18,951
I'll second that motion.

107
00:10:19,035 --> 00:10:20,369
Find Julia first.

108
00:10:21,287 --> 00:10:22,663
She still loves you.

109
00:10:27,168 --> 00:10:28,252
Does she know?

110
00:10:29,128 --> 00:10:30,212
[Gren] That you're alive?

111
00:10:31,505 --> 00:10:32,965
She figured it out.

112
00:10:33,049 --> 00:10:35,259
And knowing is gonna get her killed.

113
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:39,138
I'll make sure she's safe.

114
00:10:41,891 --> 00:10:44,393
It's a long overdue promise
I need to make good on.

115
00:10:47,897 --> 00:10:49,398
Then you're gonna need this.

116
00:10:49,482 --> 00:10:51,400
- [Jet] Don't move!
- Put the gun down.

117
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:53,986
[Jet] I said drop it. Now!

118
00:10:54,654 --> 00:10:55,988
Same goes for you, lovelies.

119
00:10:56,072 --> 00:10:59,283
Hey, hey, hey. Nobody needs to be
pointing any weapons right now.

120
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:01,410
Okay? Hey. Easy.

121
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:05,039
They're with me. So are they.

122
00:11:06,290 --> 00:11:07,750
Faye, come on.

123
00:11:09,001 --> 00:11:11,504
Faye? Come on, put the weapon down.

124
00:11:14,882 --> 00:11:16,717
What the hell? We thought you were dead.

125
00:11:17,301 --> 00:11:18,678
Yeah, I get that a lot.

126
00:11:22,139 --> 00:11:24,475
Jet, come on.

127
00:11:36,028 --> 00:11:37,905
Hey, listen, I...

128
00:11:38,572 --> 00:11:39,782
[grunts]

129
00:11:39,865 --> 00:11:41,742
Hurt... hurting me.

130
00:11:42,785 --> 00:11:45,413
I'm sorry. Thought I'd lost you, partner.

131
00:11:45,496 --> 00:11:46,747
Yeah. [chuckles]

132
00:11:46,831 --> 00:11:48,416
Glad to see you're still kicking.

133
00:11:48,499 --> 00:11:51,252
Hey, whatever happened to
that unkillable super assassin?

134
00:11:51,335 --> 00:11:52,335
Um...

135
00:11:52,962 --> 00:11:53,962
Yeah, I killed him.

136
00:11:54,505 --> 00:11:55,548
Oh. Nice.

137
00:11:55,631 --> 00:11:57,591
- [cell phone buzzing]
- Shit. Give me a minute.

138
00:11:58,300 --> 00:11:59,300
It's Kimmie.

139
00:12:00,678 --> 00:12:03,222
Hey, bean. I can't talk right now, but...

140
00:12:04,056 --> 00:12:06,934
Is this an open bar, by chance?

141
00:12:07,017 --> 00:12:08,936
Oh, you're a fun one, aren't you?

142
00:12:09,895 --> 00:12:11,147
The fucking funnest.

143
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:12,230
[laughs]

144
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:19,864
Jet?

145
00:12:22,032 --> 00:12:23,032
Jet?

146
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:26,746
- Who the fuck are you?
- [grunts]

147
00:12:28,789 --> 00:12:29,874
Jet!

148
00:12:29,957 --> 00:12:31,268
Oh, I thought we'd moved beyond this.

149
00:12:31,292 --> 00:12:32,752
- They took her.
- Who?

150
00:12:32,835 --> 00:12:33,836
Kimmie!

151
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:37,131
Goddamn Syndicate kidnapped her
from Europa.

152
00:12:37,214 --> 00:12:40,217
Took her right out of school.
They want to exchange her for him.

153
00:12:40,718 --> 00:12:43,929
Except they didn't call him Spike.
They called you Fearless.

154
00:12:45,222 --> 00:12:46,140
Who are you?

155
00:12:46,223 --> 00:12:48,984
And why does the Syndicate want
to use my daughter to get to you, huh?

156
00:12:50,478 --> 00:12:51,896
The man who took Kimmie...

157
00:12:53,689 --> 00:12:56,692
His name is Vicious. He was my partner.

158
00:13:00,070 --> 00:13:02,281
Back when I killed people
for the Syndicate.

159
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:05,701
- What?
- You son of a...

160
00:13:06,368 --> 00:13:07,912
You're a goddamn hit man?

161
00:13:08,746 --> 00:13:10,664
All this shit about ex-military?

162
00:13:10,748 --> 00:13:12,348
- I never said that.
- [Jet] You never...

163
00:13:12,416 --> 00:13:13,793
You let me believe it.

164
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:17,755
God damn. You're a Syndicate hit man.

165
00:13:17,838 --> 00:13:21,509
Was. They've been trying to kill me
ever since they found out I'm still alive.

166
00:13:21,592 --> 00:13:24,261
I'm gonna save them the trouble
and kill you myself.

167
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:25,346
You could.

168
00:13:26,138 --> 00:13:28,808
Yeah. You'd be right to.

169
00:13:28,891 --> 00:13:30,351
But you need me.

170
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:33,646
To barter for Kimmie's life.

171
00:13:35,731 --> 00:13:36,565
[clicks]

172
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:37,858
[breath trembling]

173
00:13:39,777 --> 00:13:41,403
You don't hand me over to Vicious,

174
00:13:42,822 --> 00:13:44,448
he's gonna kill her.

175
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:55,042
Fine. Let's get this over with.

176
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:58,462
Spike, if you should
find your way out of this...

177
00:13:58,546 --> 00:13:59,713
I wouldn't count on it.

178
00:13:59,797 --> 00:14:00,881
Julia needs you.

179
00:14:01,757 --> 00:14:02,842
Time to clear out.

180
00:14:02,925 --> 00:14:04,565
- [Jet] Let's go.
- It's not safe anymore.

181
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:06,470
I'll survive.

182
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:08,806
I always do.

183
00:14:18,649 --> 00:14:20,901
[Jet] You try and run,
it's gonna be bad for you.

184
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:22,361
[Spike] I'm done running.

185
00:14:22,444 --> 00:14:24,524
He told you
the fish factory for the exchange, right?

186
00:14:24,572 --> 00:14:25,573
Yeah.

187
00:14:25,656 --> 00:14:27,616
- I know that place.
- I'll bet you do.

188
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,911
Listen, we can get around the guards,
if we can manage...

189
00:14:30,995 --> 00:14:33,873
- [grunts]
- Jet! What are you doing?

190
00:14:34,748 --> 00:14:36,125
There's a better way!

191
00:14:39,461 --> 00:14:40,462
You can't turn him in.

192
00:14:40,546 --> 00:14:42,631
Don't kid yourself. This is happening.

193
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:45,759
You know we can get her back
if we work together.

194
00:14:46,552 --> 00:14:48,196
You think I'm gonna
risk my daughter's life

195
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:51,599
on the word of Spike Spiegel, or Fearless,
or whatever the hell his name is?

196
00:14:51,682 --> 00:14:53,893
- You can't.
- I will.

197
00:14:55,394 --> 00:14:56,394
I won't.

198
00:14:56,896 --> 00:15:01,859
You know, he might be a dick,
but he risked his life for mine.

199
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:05,404
Risked his life for yours.
Many times over, I'm sure of it.

200
00:15:05,487 --> 00:15:07,948
He knew the rules. No lies.

201
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:10,993
He could have come clean with me.
He could have walked away from me.

202
00:15:11,076 --> 00:15:13,037
He could have done
a million things he didn't.

203
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,455
What did he do?

204
00:15:14,538 --> 00:15:16,624
He put my daughter's life
in a killer's hands.

205
00:15:16,707 --> 00:15:18,584
By my math, the slate is clean.

206
00:15:19,251 --> 00:15:21,211
It's his life for Kimmie's.
That's the play.

207
00:15:21,295 --> 00:15:23,923
Well, that fucked-up math doesn't add up.

208
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:28,302
I won't carry that weight.

209
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:31,096
[soulful music playing]

210
00:16:00,876 --> 00:16:04,630
[whispers] You know he's not gonna
let you live after this, right?

211
00:16:06,548 --> 00:16:10,636
You're the only one who knows
why Vicious really tried to kill Fearless.

212
00:17:05,190 --> 00:17:06,442
[song ends]

213
00:17:09,862 --> 00:17:11,488
Did you ever love Vicious?

214
00:17:14,783 --> 00:17:15,993
I thought I did.

215
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:21,498
And then I realized
I didn't know what love was.

216
00:17:22,499 --> 00:17:23,917
Until it was too late.

217
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:29,256
Until Fearless.

218
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:36,555
Then you should be with him.

219
00:17:37,806 --> 00:17:39,224
[choking]

220
00:17:40,684 --> 00:17:41,852
[tires screech]

221
00:17:43,645 --> 00:17:44,772
[Julia screams]

222
00:18:13,675 --> 00:18:15,010
Evening, Officer.

223
00:18:15,803 --> 00:18:18,180
It's going to be okay, honey. I'm here.

224
00:18:20,307 --> 00:18:22,101
[breathing shakily]

225
00:18:22,184 --> 00:18:23,936
Everything's gonna be okay.

226
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:26,646
Do you have him?

227
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:29,482
He's in the trunk.

228
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:33,070
He didn't exactly come willingly.

229
00:18:34,404 --> 00:18:35,614
Look, if he's not there,

230
00:18:36,740 --> 00:18:39,535
you've got enough guys here
to show me the error of my ways.

231
00:19:00,264 --> 00:19:01,306
Spike!

232
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:02,391
Now!

233
00:19:23,662 --> 00:19:24,663
No.

234
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:27,207
Shit.

235
00:19:30,627 --> 00:19:31,837
See you soon, Spike.

236
00:19:55,777 --> 00:19:56,987
[metal creaking]

237
00:20:02,451 --> 00:20:03,451
[sputtering]

238
00:20:07,456 --> 00:20:08,749
[Julia breathing heavily]

239
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:11,542
[Julia gasps]

240
00:20:12,711 --> 00:20:13,712
[weakly] Find him.

241
00:20:19,676 --> 00:20:21,094
[Julia grunting]

242
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:29,686
[panting]

243
00:21:13,313 --> 00:21:14,648
[groaning]

244
00:21:21,571 --> 00:21:22,739
[Spike] Oh, good, you're up.

245
00:21:26,910 --> 00:21:29,871
I was getting worried you were gonna
sleep through my execution.

246
00:21:30,580 --> 00:21:32,124
I wouldn't want to miss that.

247
00:21:33,542 --> 00:21:34,960
How long have I been out?

248
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:37,796
[Spike] A couple of hours.

249
00:21:37,879 --> 00:21:38,964
[panting]

250
00:21:42,592 --> 00:21:43,635
Where are we?

251
00:21:46,555 --> 00:21:47,889
[Spike] Ninth ring of Hell.

252
00:21:51,268 --> 00:21:53,270
[groans, pants]

253
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:56,148
Hey.

254
00:21:58,984 --> 00:21:59,984
Thank you.

255
00:22:00,902 --> 00:22:01,902
For what?

256
00:22:02,821 --> 00:22:05,907
Prolonging your lousy life
a few more miserable minutes?

257
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,493
For changing your mind on me.

258
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:11,288
[scoffs]

259
00:22:13,123 --> 00:22:15,459
For giving me a chance
to make right on my wrongs.

260
00:22:15,542 --> 00:22:17,377
Yeah, didn't work out so good.

261
00:22:18,754 --> 00:22:20,339
For either of us.

262
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:23,008
We've seen worse.

263
00:22:25,052 --> 00:22:26,053
Have we?

264
00:22:26,762 --> 00:22:27,971
[door opens]

265
00:22:36,396 --> 00:22:39,483
When angels are forced out of Heaven,

266
00:22:40,442 --> 00:22:41,902
they become devils.

267
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:47,157
You agree, don't you? Spike?

268
00:22:47,741 --> 00:22:50,077
Where's Kimmie?
If you hurt her, I swear before God...

269
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:51,036
[Vicious] Hurt her?

270
00:22:51,119 --> 00:22:52,120
[laughs]

271
00:22:53,330 --> 00:22:54,706
I would never hurt a kid.

272
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:57,834
No kids.

273
00:22:59,544 --> 00:23:00,544
Isn't that right?

274
00:23:02,297 --> 00:23:07,010
And everyone fancied you... the angel.

275
00:23:08,595 --> 00:23:10,639
[softly] Only when standing at your side.

276
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:13,975
I'm the Devil?

277
00:23:16,353 --> 00:23:17,813
Stop me when I'm wrong.

278
00:23:17,896 --> 00:23:20,941
Spike is a liar. A betrayer.

279
00:23:21,024 --> 00:23:25,570
He cares only about himself
and death follows him wherever he goes.

280
00:23:25,654 --> 00:23:27,155
Sound like an angel to you?

281
00:23:27,239 --> 00:23:28,907
I just want my daughter.

282
00:23:31,201 --> 00:23:33,036
[Vicious breathing heavily]

283
00:23:36,832 --> 00:23:40,001
I gave you a space in my family's crypt.

284
00:23:41,211 --> 00:23:42,379
Did you know that?

285
00:23:42,462 --> 00:23:46,341
I used to come down here
after you betrayed me

286
00:23:46,425 --> 00:23:47,884
to mourn what I'd lost.

287
00:23:50,095 --> 00:23:51,596
To mourn you.

288
00:23:54,182 --> 00:23:56,393
But I found I had no tears to weep.

289
00:24:02,399 --> 00:24:03,442
Bring the girl.

290
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:07,779
Thank you. Thank you.

291
00:24:07,863 --> 00:24:08,989
[Vicious laughing]

292
00:24:10,282 --> 00:24:11,783
Oh, how delightful.

293
00:24:13,827 --> 00:24:15,829
You actually think I'm letting her go?

294
00:24:15,912 --> 00:24:16,830
[grunts]

295
00:24:16,913 --> 00:24:20,375
See, Spike and I are both devils.

296
00:24:20,459 --> 00:24:22,919
The difference is, I'm honest about it.

297
00:24:23,003 --> 00:24:25,380
- You said you wouldn't hurt her.
- I won't.

298
00:24:26,423 --> 00:24:28,717
- I'll kill her.
- God damn, you piece of shit!

299
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:30,385
[yells]

300
00:24:30,469 --> 00:24:31,803
[groaning]

301
00:24:38,727 --> 00:24:40,937
Ever since I learned you're alive,

302
00:24:41,021 --> 00:24:45,358
all I could think about
was putting you in that empty hole.

303
00:24:45,442 --> 00:24:47,402
[Jet breathing heavily]

304
00:24:47,486 --> 00:24:49,196
You should have just died that night.

305
00:24:49,279 --> 00:24:51,656
Or you should have
killed yourself for what you did!

306
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:52,824
Look at me!

307
00:24:55,285 --> 00:24:57,078
You were supposed to be my brother.

308
00:24:58,914 --> 00:25:00,749
You were supposed to love me!

309
00:25:00,832 --> 00:25:03,460
I was supposed to end you.

310
00:25:05,337 --> 00:25:07,005
I will not make that mistake again.

311
00:25:09,799 --> 00:25:11,134
[Kimmie crying]

312
00:25:12,135 --> 00:25:13,135
[Jet] Kimmie!

313
00:25:13,845 --> 00:25:16,097
I've got you, bean. I've got you.

314
00:25:16,181 --> 00:25:18,892
- I'm scared.
- I know, baby. I know.

315
00:25:20,936 --> 00:25:22,187
[grunting]

316
00:25:23,647 --> 00:25:25,315
[yells, groans]

317
00:25:29,945 --> 00:25:32,822
This is where you die... for the last time.

318
00:25:32,906 --> 00:25:34,491
[breathing heavily]

319
00:25:36,117 --> 00:25:41,122
But you're gonna watch
your partner and his brat die first.

320
00:25:42,624 --> 00:25:46,169
Look at me. Look at me.
It's gonna be okay.

321
00:25:47,254 --> 00:25:48,922
[Kimmie crying] Dad, I wanna go home.

322
00:25:49,005 --> 00:25:52,300
Okay, it's gonna be okay.
It's gonna be okay.

323
00:25:56,680 --> 00:25:58,098
It's okay, baby.

324
00:25:58,848 --> 00:26:01,643
It's gonna be okay, baby. Okay?

325
00:26:07,107 --> 00:26:09,109
[thrilling instrumental music playing]

326
00:26:18,535 --> 00:26:19,911
[men grunting]

327
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:28,044
[grunts]

328
00:26:38,054 --> 00:26:40,807
Welcome to the ouch, motherfuckers!

329
00:26:40,890 --> 00:26:42,809
[laughs maniacally]

330
00:27:13,632 --> 00:27:14,716
[mouths] Fuck.

331
00:27:32,942 --> 00:27:33,777
Come on.

332
00:27:33,860 --> 00:27:34,944
[grunts]

333
00:27:37,155 --> 00:27:38,156
I'll be all right.

334
00:27:38,823 --> 00:27:39,823
I got her.

335
00:27:40,325 --> 00:27:41,868
I got you. I got you.

336
00:27:47,123 --> 00:27:49,125
[spaceship landing]

337
00:27:49,209 --> 00:27:50,210
[Jet grunts]

338
00:28:03,431 --> 00:28:05,058
- [man grunts]
- [Kimmie gasps]

339
00:28:05,767 --> 00:28:07,143
- [Spike yells]
- [man grunts]

340
00:28:08,561 --> 00:28:09,729
[Spike groans]

341
00:28:12,941 --> 00:28:13,941
Let's go.

342
00:28:33,837 --> 00:28:35,606
- Here you go, sweetheart.
- [Faye] Come on, kiddo.

343
00:28:35,630 --> 00:28:37,298
Thought you didn't like the math.

344
00:28:38,299 --> 00:28:39,676
You're both idiots.

345
00:28:40,218 --> 00:28:43,513
But I couldn't get good on you
knuckledusters dying a dipshit death.

346
00:28:44,264 --> 00:28:45,348
- Come on.
- [Faye] Come on.

347
00:28:46,391 --> 00:28:47,391
[grunts]

348
00:28:49,394 --> 00:28:50,228
[Jet groans]

349
00:28:50,311 --> 00:28:51,896
Okay. Come on.

350
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:54,607
I'm not finished here.

351
00:28:54,691 --> 00:28:57,777
- What? Are you stupid?
- Let him go.

352
00:29:01,364 --> 00:29:02,532
Get them outta here.

353
00:29:04,993 --> 00:29:05,994
[Faye] Spike.

354
00:29:07,620 --> 00:29:09,581
Shoot them before they shoot you, huh?

355
00:29:11,958 --> 00:29:13,543
I'll see you around, Valentine.

356
00:29:17,422 --> 00:29:19,466
- [controls beep]
- [spaceship powering up]

357
00:29:23,303 --> 00:29:25,305
["Rain" playing]

358
00:30:01,549 --> 00:30:03,968
[Vicious] Did you come back
to beg for their lives?

359
00:30:04,052 --> 00:30:06,721
Mercy's for the weak! Remember?

360
00:30:08,306 --> 00:30:10,308
[song continues]

361
00:30:22,654 --> 00:30:23,863
[grunts]

362
00:30:46,135 --> 00:30:47,135
[man grunts]

363
00:30:58,690 --> 00:31:00,316
[music fades]

364
00:31:06,239 --> 00:31:07,240
[metal scrapes]

365
00:31:07,323 --> 00:31:08,408
[both grunting]

366
00:31:20,044 --> 00:31:21,713
[Vicious yells]

367
00:31:25,425 --> 00:31:27,427
[dramatic music playing]

368
00:32:02,170 --> 00:32:03,630
[both grunting]

369
00:32:06,215 --> 00:32:07,342
[Vicious yells]

370
00:32:11,971 --> 00:32:13,723
[both grunting]

371
00:32:22,565 --> 00:32:24,400
[both panting]

372
00:32:27,570 --> 00:32:28,780
You should see yourself.

373
00:32:30,323 --> 00:32:33,201
Do you have any idea what you look like
right at this moment, Spike?

374
00:32:33,701 --> 00:32:34,535
What?

375
00:32:34,619 --> 00:32:35,995
A ravenous beast.

376
00:32:37,413 --> 00:32:39,707
The same blood runs through both of us.

377
00:32:39,791 --> 00:32:43,836
The blood of a beast who wanders,
hunting for the blood of others.

378
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:46,047
I've bled all that kind of blood away.

379
00:32:46,130 --> 00:32:47,548
Then why are you still alive?

380
00:32:47,632 --> 00:32:48,632
[Spike screams]

381
00:32:50,301 --> 00:32:52,220
[continues screaming]

382
00:32:56,432 --> 00:32:57,558
[Vicious groans]

383
00:33:05,024 --> 00:33:06,067
[sword clatters]

384
00:33:12,949 --> 00:33:13,949
[gunshot]

385
00:33:20,164 --> 00:33:21,791
[Spike breathing heavily]

386
00:33:21,874 --> 00:33:22,875
[groans]

387
00:33:28,464 --> 00:33:29,507
[exhales]

388
00:33:31,968 --> 00:33:33,970
[Vicious groaning]

389
00:33:35,555 --> 00:33:36,556
Julia.

390
00:33:38,266 --> 00:33:39,392
It's true.

391
00:33:42,603 --> 00:33:43,938
Are you okay?

392
00:33:45,481 --> 00:33:46,607
I am now.

393
00:33:49,402 --> 00:33:50,778
I've dreamt of you.

394
00:33:51,738 --> 00:33:52,739
Have you?

395
00:33:55,116 --> 00:33:56,117
Endlessly.

396
00:33:59,412 --> 00:34:01,080
Then why didn't you come for me?

397
00:34:05,376 --> 00:34:07,837
All these years, you...
you knew where I was.

398
00:34:09,839 --> 00:34:11,924
Yet you let me languish with him.

399
00:34:14,135 --> 00:34:15,178
Why?

400
00:34:15,261 --> 00:34:17,055
[Vicious laughs, groans]

401
00:34:17,722 --> 00:34:21,559
Because I told him you chose me.

402
00:34:21,642 --> 00:34:22,643
[laughs]

403
00:34:24,687 --> 00:34:26,272
And you believed him?

404
00:34:28,107 --> 00:34:29,108
I shouldn't have.

405
00:34:31,402 --> 00:34:32,402
I'm sorry.

406
00:34:33,071 --> 00:34:34,530
But now we can make it right.

407
00:34:35,323 --> 00:34:37,533
We can be free of all of this.

408
00:34:37,617 --> 00:34:39,202
Of him. The Syndicate, we can...

409
00:34:39,285 --> 00:34:40,965
[Julia] Why would I want to be free of it?

410
00:34:41,579 --> 00:34:43,956
Right at the moment
when I've captured the throne.

411
00:34:44,665 --> 00:34:45,875
[Julia exhales]

412
00:34:46,459 --> 00:34:50,546
With the Elders dead and the Capos gone,

413
00:34:52,131 --> 00:34:56,177
all that's in the way
of controlling the Syndicate is him.

414
00:35:00,848 --> 00:35:02,517
Finish the jackal.

415
00:35:03,476 --> 00:35:08,773
Carry his head on a pike to the temple.
And the rule will be ours.

416
00:35:16,948 --> 00:35:17,949
No.

417
00:35:19,367 --> 00:35:20,827
That life, I told you...

418
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:23,871
I don't want it anymore.

419
00:35:26,332 --> 00:35:27,667
What about what I want?

420
00:35:27,750 --> 00:35:30,920
- Julia...
- I'm done being scared.

421
00:35:31,003 --> 00:35:32,380
This isn't you.

422
00:35:33,089 --> 00:35:35,299
You made me who I am.

423
00:35:35,383 --> 00:35:36,467
No. No, Julia...

424
00:35:36,551 --> 00:35:39,428
Leaving me with him to fend for myself.

425
00:35:39,512 --> 00:35:41,681
[laughing weakly]

426
00:35:41,764 --> 00:35:43,599
To live in endless terror,

427
00:35:43,683 --> 00:35:46,185
wondering if today's the day
he tires of me

428
00:35:46,269 --> 00:35:48,146
and tosses me from the window.

429
00:35:51,691 --> 00:35:52,942
You made me.

430
00:35:54,569 --> 00:35:55,653
I loved you.

431
00:35:56,529 --> 00:35:58,239
I never stopped loving you.

432
00:36:01,993 --> 00:36:03,077
That may be.

433
00:36:06,539 --> 00:36:07,790
But it's clear now.

434
00:36:12,795 --> 00:36:16,215
You are nothing more than a dream
I needed to wake up from.

435
00:36:28,769 --> 00:36:31,189
[chorus singing]

436
00:37:20,571 --> 00:37:21,739
Kimmie!

437
00:37:22,615 --> 00:37:24,450
- [Kimmie] Mommy!
- Oh, baby!

438
00:37:24,533 --> 00:37:25,952
[gasps in relief]

439
00:37:31,290 --> 00:37:33,501
Daddy! I want to go home.

440
00:37:33,584 --> 00:37:34,669
[Chalmers] Come here.

441
00:37:40,925 --> 00:37:44,220
[car doors open and close]

442
00:37:44,303 --> 00:37:46,055
[car engine starts]

443
00:38:01,237 --> 00:38:02,280
[sighs]

444
00:38:25,553 --> 00:38:26,721
I'm all packed up.

445
00:38:28,097 --> 00:38:29,098
Yeah.

446
00:38:30,975 --> 00:38:32,059
I'm headed out.

447
00:38:34,186 --> 00:38:35,186
Yeah.

448
00:38:43,654 --> 00:38:46,574
I know you're going through
a lot of shit right now, but...

449
00:38:48,743 --> 00:38:50,745
I have a chance to find out who I am.

450
00:38:52,538 --> 00:38:53,622
You should do that.

451
00:38:59,128 --> 00:39:00,379
You need to do that.

452
00:39:25,988 --> 00:39:27,365
[Jet inhales deeply]

453
00:39:28,324 --> 00:39:29,742
[exhales]

454
00:39:43,422 --> 00:39:44,423
[groans]

455
00:39:48,677 --> 00:39:49,845
[groans louder]

456
00:39:50,429 --> 00:39:51,639
[breathing heavily]

457
00:39:54,016 --> 00:39:55,518
[groans]

458
00:40:10,574 --> 00:40:11,574
What?

459
00:40:12,034 --> 00:40:13,411
Hello, Vicious.

460
00:40:16,330 --> 00:40:18,040
[growls]

461
00:40:20,584 --> 00:40:21,710
You're dead.

462
00:40:24,463 --> 00:40:26,674
I'm head of the Syndicate.
My people will...

463
00:40:26,757 --> 00:40:27,757
Will what?

464
00:40:30,136 --> 00:40:34,432
You're an Elder now.
And no one is allowed to see the Elders.

465
00:40:37,309 --> 00:40:40,563
As your wife,
I'll be speaking on your behalf.

466
00:40:43,774 --> 00:40:44,859
So really...

467
00:40:44,942 --> 00:40:46,152
[sighs]

468
00:40:51,615 --> 00:40:53,534
I don't think we need you at all.

469
00:41:03,627 --> 00:41:05,254
[breathing heavily]

470
00:41:10,176 --> 00:41:11,177
Julia...

471
00:41:13,762 --> 00:41:14,762
Julia.

472
00:41:19,435 --> 00:41:21,020
- [gun clicks]
- [gasps]

473
00:41:23,063 --> 00:41:24,482
[chuckles softly]

474
00:41:28,444 --> 00:41:29,737
We'll try again tomorrow.

475
00:41:29,820 --> 00:41:32,156
[sultry jazz music playing]

476
00:41:38,787 --> 00:41:40,331
[door closes]

477
00:41:40,414 --> 00:41:42,875
[yells] No!

478
00:41:56,555 --> 00:41:57,806
[groans softly]

479
00:42:02,811 --> 00:42:03,811
[scoffs]

480
00:42:08,359 --> 00:42:09,527
I knew you'd survive.

481
00:42:12,029 --> 00:42:13,489
It's what cockroaches do.

482
00:42:15,199 --> 00:42:16,200
Jet.

483
00:42:19,411 --> 00:42:23,499
The only reason you're still alive
is you helped save Kimmie.

484
00:42:25,543 --> 00:42:29,880
Your buddy, Vicious, was right.

485
00:42:31,924 --> 00:42:33,801
Death follows you wherever you go.

486
00:42:36,804 --> 00:42:38,681
It's in your bones, Spike.

487
00:42:51,610 --> 00:42:52,820
If I ever see you again,

488
00:42:54,572 --> 00:42:55,656
I <i>will</i> kill you.

489
00:42:56,407 --> 00:42:58,409
[music continues]

490
00:43:22,391 --> 00:43:23,809
[spaceship door closing]

491
00:43:46,332 --> 00:43:48,334
[music ends]

492
00:43:53,005 --> 00:43:55,007
[guitar music playing]

493
00:43:59,470 --> 00:44:00,888
[grunts]

494
00:44:01,597 --> 00:44:03,015
[woman shouts indistinctly]

495
00:44:09,229 --> 00:44:10,230
[glass shatters]

496
00:44:45,432 --> 00:44:47,810
[Ed] Spike! [giggles]

497
00:44:47,893 --> 00:44:49,853
Spike Spiegel!

498
00:44:50,979 --> 00:44:54,858
No... Spike Spiegel.

499
00:44:56,652 --> 00:44:57,569
Not anymore.

500
00:44:57,653 --> 00:44:58,862
Yes, you are.

501
00:44:59,488 --> 00:45:03,158
You're Spike, cowboy,
bounty hunter for hire!

502
00:45:03,242 --> 00:45:05,953
Wake up! I have a job for you!

503
00:45:06,495 --> 00:45:08,038
A bounty!

504
00:45:09,498 --> 00:45:10,332
What?

505
00:45:10,416 --> 00:45:12,918
Bad man, big reward!

506
00:45:13,001 --> 00:45:15,963
We have to find the Butterfly Man.
Ooh! Danger, danger!

507
00:45:16,046 --> 00:45:17,047
Too loud.

508
00:45:17,131 --> 00:45:22,302
We have to find Volaju Volaju Volaju
before he does spooky, bad things.

509
00:45:23,095 --> 00:45:24,095
Shut up.

510
00:45:25,806 --> 00:45:26,807
[grunts]

511
00:45:37,651 --> 00:45:40,946
Spike? [softly] Spike.

512
00:45:42,156 --> 00:45:43,240
Hello?

513
00:45:43,991 --> 00:45:45,284
[whispers] Wake up!

514
00:45:46,201 --> 00:45:47,619
[yells] <i>Spike!</i>

515
00:45:51,206 --> 00:45:53,125
[upbeat jazz music playing]
